  "text": "Similar results were also obtained by El Ali and colleagues [CITATION_1] . In their work, they evaluated attenuation correction in small animals showing an underestimation of true activity concentration of about 10%-20%. They also showed that PETbased and CT-based methods provide comparable results for attenuation compensation in PET while uniform AC method may be applied only if less accuracy is acceptable.",
